Daio Paper Chairman Steps Down After Borrowing Company Money

-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 
2011-09-16T06:31:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/daio-paper-chairman-steps-down-after-borrowing-company-money.html
Daio Paper Corp. (3880) , a Japanese paper
maker, said Chairman Mototaka Ikawa stepped down today after
borrowing 5 billion yen ($65 million) from an affiliate.  The company is investigating the matter, according to a
statement to the Tokyo Stock Exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
